<img src="/print/global_images2005/spacer.gif" alt="" width="1" height="30" hspace="0" vspace="0" border="0"><br>

<img src="/print/global_images2005/2.0.line.gif" alt="-----------------------------------------------" width="590" height="2" hspace="0" vspace="0" border="0"><br>
<img src="/print/global_images2005/spacer.gif" alt="" width="1" height="5" hspace="0" vspace="0" border="0"><br>

<span class="subhead">Consumer Robotics </span><br>
<span class="text_colored">Sands Expo and Convention Center</span>
<br>Sponsor(s): <span class="text_colored">Metapo, Ologic, Robotics Trends</span>

<br><br>

<IMG height=113 hspace=6 src="/print/images/partners/robotics.gif" width=115 align=right>Personal, service and mobile robotics are completely new technology markets, and all will have a major impact on the way we live our daily lives. The upside potential for product and service providers serving these markets is nearly boundless. However, for product companies and solution providers to maximize their potential for success in the mobile robotics market, as well as grow the market as a whole, they must be able to identify, meet with and educate prospective customers and partners more effectively and rapidly than their competitors. Produced by Robotics Trends.<BR><BR><STRONG>Who should exhibit here?<BR></STRONG>The <STRONG>Robotics TechZone</STRONG> is specifically for producers of personal, service and mobile robots and robotics technology seeking: 
